<TITLE> Suspect package recovered near Khaleda's office </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Feb 15 (bdnews24.com)  Police recovered a suspicious package in front of BNP chairperson Khaleda Zia's Gulshan office Monday morning, which looked like the type of crude explosive device commonly called a 'cocktail', a party official said. Ahmed Kabir, sub-inspector of Gulshan Police Station said they recovered the package wrapped in red scotch tape some 200 yards from the opposition leader's office. "The office caretaker found the 'cocktail' in front of the gate at around 6:30am and informed police of the matter," opposition chief whip Zainal Abdin Farroque told bdnews24.com. Police came and took it to the station, he said. Farroque said BNP will hold a press conference at parliament's media centre later in the afternoon. bdne
